[A long time ago, in a galaxy far, far away, Karl Johnson hypothesized that
VS viruses might really be plant viruses. As I recall, his thinking was
that many plant viruses are transmitted by plant-feeding arthropods, that
male mosquitoes also feed on plants, and that, perhaps by venereal
transmission (to breeding partners, which take blood meals), male
mosquitoes might introduce a plant virus to the vertebrate world. It
remains a fascinating hypothesis. Thanks to the marvelous Bob Tesh for the
historical perspective and, in the manner of the good Professor, providing
germane references. Now, if we can just get him into a tweed jacket with
patched elbows ... - Mod.CHC
